With his electrifying mastery of slide guitar coupled with his capacity for superior live performances, Rogers has won consistent critical acclaim for his consummate studio work as well as his deft ability to bring the house down during live shows with his band, the Delta Rhythm Kings.

Roy Rogers has been on the Billboard charts consistently with each new CD release, and has been featured in Rolling Stone, People Magazine, USA Today, Guitar Player, Acoustic Guitar, Blues Revue and many other media outlets for decades.  His consistent and exhilarating live performances have helped him to receive worldwide acclaim as one of the best slide guitar players performing today.  He has garnered multiple Grammy (8) nominations for his work as a songwriter and producer for his one-time boss John Lee Hooker and for  friend Ramblin' Jack Elliott, and he's received numerous accolades  for  songwriting (with Bonnie Raitt and others) and his work on movie soundtracks and television.  Rogers has performed with Carlos Santana, Bonnie Raitt, Linda Ronstadt, Steve Miller, John Lee Hooker, Ramblin' Jack Elliott, Sammy Hagar and many others.

"Rogers is both a sensational and a sensitive blues guitarist - certainly among the finest slide guitarists playing today. His wailing slide guitar sound (and churning rhythms, when needed) mark him and his work as of the highest caliber."

- San Francisco Chronicle
